.TH "jbd2_journal_get_write_access" 9 "jbd2_journal_get_write_access" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
jbd2_journal_get_write_access \- notify intent to modify a buffer for metadata (not data) update.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" jbd2_journal_get_write_access
.BI "(handle_t *handle "  ","
.BI "struct buffer_head *bh "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "handle" 12
transaction to add buffer modifications to
.IP "bh" 12
bh to be used for metadata writes
.SH "RETURN"
error code or 0 on success.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
In full data journalling mode the buffer may be of type BJ_AsyncData,
because we're ``\fBwrite\fPing`` a buffer which is also part of a shared mapping.
